cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning (RL) and the use of procedurally generated environments to benchmark RL algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary subfield of RL. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to generate the environments, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the graphics and visual aspects of the environments, which could place it in cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of RL in control systems, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
